splitdnsd (0.2.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * splitdns-notify: socket-activated relay (--listen) + built-in client (--relay)
    so an unprivileged DHCP lease hook can trigger a signed announce without the TSIG
    key or a socat dependency. Ships splitdns-notify-relay.socket/.service and a Kea
    hook example.

 -- gutschke <gutschke@users.noreply.github.com>  Fri, 04 Jul 2026 00:00:00 -0700

splitdnsd (0.2.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Encrypted client DNS (DoT/DoH) with DDR auto-upgrade advertising (opt-in).
  * Local plane: .lan/.local names from mDNS, on-demand resolution, unicast DNS-SD.
  * Diagnostics console: mDNS host enrichment, Encrypted & DDR panel, transport query tool.
  * Security hardening: diagnostics control CSRF header, TSIG replay protection.

 -- gutschke <gutschke@users.noreply.github.com>  Fri, 03 Jul 2026 00:00:00 -0700

